            <div class="article_content">
            
                <div class="article_header layout_row marginate_small">
                    
                        
                            
                            
                        
                    
                    <div class="article_title_and_info">
                        <div class="article_title"><h2>The world's mightiest armies</h2></div>
                        <div class="padding_top_small"></div>
                        <div class="separator_horizontal"></div>
                        <div class="padding_bottom_small"></div>
                        <div>The DE international affairs department, 07:01</div>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <div class="article_body">
                    
                    <div class="article_body_text">
                        Leading international military experts estimate the following nations to be the strongest military powers:<br>
1st : <span class="func_country_link clickable" data-player-id="351">East Cuba</span> (0.7%)<br>
2nd : <span class="func_country_link clickable" data-player-id="363">Edmonton</span> (0.63%)<br>
3rd : <span class="func_country_link clickable" data-player-id="704">Podolia &amp; Bessarabia</span> (0.58%)<br>
4th : <span class="func_country_link clickable" data-player-id="31">Aragon</span> (0.58%)<br>
5th : <span class="func_country_link clickable" data-player-id="477">Eucla</span> (0.5%)<br>
6th : <span class="func_country_link clickable" data-player-id="252">South Madagascar</span> (0.48%)<br>
7th : <span class="func_country_link clickable" data-player-id="376">Port Arthur</span> (0.47%)<br>
8th : <span class="func_country_link clickable" data-player-id="536">Luzon</span> (0.46%)<br>
9th : <span class="func_country_link clickable" data-player-id="192">Natal</span> (0.46%)<br>
